---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="API Documentation">
  <h1>API Documentation</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
    The API documentation is generated from TypeScript source code using TypeDoc.
  </p>
  
  <h2>Core Functions</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-2">
    <li><a href="#load" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>load()</code></a> - Load an HTML/XML string</li>
    <li><a href="#loadBuffer" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>loadBuffer()</code></a> - Load from a buffer</li>
    <li><a href="#fromURL" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>fromURL()</code></a> - Load from a URL</li>
    <li><a href="#stringStream" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>stringStream()</code></a> - Parse from a string stream</li>
    <li><a href="#decodeStream" class="text-primary hover:underline"><code>decodeStream()</code></a> - Parse from an encoded stream</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Cheerio Class</h2>
  <p>
    The <code>Cheerio</code> class provides jQuery-like methods for traversing and manipulating the DOM.
    See the <a href="https://github.com/cheeriojs/cheerio#api" class="text-primary hover:underline">GitHub README</a> for a complete list of available methods.
  </p>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <p>
    Cheerio accepts various options for parsing and rendering. See the 
    <a href="/docs/advanced/configuring-cheerio" class="text-primary hover:underline">Configuring Cheerio</a> 
    guide for details.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
